value.value: A shape quality inhering on a bearer by virtue of a bearer's shape lacking in pattern or uniformity; for example, it may have sides of different lengths, different curvatures, or unequal angles.
Cuspidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing a single cusp.
A diameter that remains constant throughout the extent of an entity.
An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is in the parasagittal plane.
An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed along the longitudinal or anterior-posterior axis.
A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of a single, maximally connected structure.

definition.value: What counts as maximally connected may be relative to some specification of granularity.

value.value: A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of multiple structures lacking any physical connection to each other.
The velocity of spatial propagation of a process. Examples include the velocity of propagation of an action potential along an axon.
A propagation velocity that is higher than normal.
A propagation velocity that is lower than normal.

A physical quality of a process that is its spatial distribution. For example, bone mineralization follows stereotypical spatial distribution patterns during development, which may be altered in some phenotypes.
A quality of a single cell inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

definition.value: Use this term for morphologies that can *only* inhere in a cell, e.g. morphological qualities inhering in a cell by virtue of the presence, location or shape of one or more cell parts.

value.value: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having multiple cilia.
A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having only one cilium.
Absence due to a degenerative process.
The ability of a process to produce its output.
A decrease in the ability of a process to produce its output.
A increase in the ability of a process to produce its output.
Slender and spirally coiled.
A quality inhering in a structure by virtue of it consisting of many of repeated, similar or identical subunits, arranged in some orderly array.

definition.value: A complete coverage of this domain would subclasses homopolymeric, copolymeric, crystalline.

value.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which the bearers stands out or projects beyond a surface or line.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the extent to which the bearer is capable of being stretched or swollen.
A quality inhering in air by virtue of the partial pressure exerted by the bearer's water vapour content.
An increase in humidity.
An decrease in humidity.

A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of roughly equal proportions of positively and negatively charged particles, having neither a defined volume nor defined shape, having internal magnetic fields, and being electrically conductive.
The degree to which the bearer is exposed to visible light.
An increase in illumination.
An decrease in illumination.
Having a shape or form that resembles a step of a stairway (e.g., a ledge or offset margin).

A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of a portion of the bearer's molecular or polymolecular constituents present in one phase being dispersed in a portion of the bearer's constituents present in another phase.
A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer's solid or liquid constituents being suspended in a gas.
A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped in the form of the letter C.
A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped in the form of the letter J.
The propensity of a material to undergo combustion. Combustion encompasses smouldering and flaming combustion. Combustibility is usually applied to solids.
An increase in porosity.
An decrease in porosity.
quality, state, or degree of being stable.
An increase in stability.
A decrease in stability.

A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer's solid or liquid constituents being transiently dispersed in a solid, liquid, or gas before settling due to gravity or centrifugal forces.
A shape that ineres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's mass being distributed in a feather-like fashion.

The presence of a constituent, impurity, or some other undesirable element that spoils, corrupts, infects, makes unfit, or makes inferior a material, physical body, natural environment, place of human occupancy, or other material entity.
An increase in contamination.
A decrease in contamination.
A biological sex quality inhering in an individual based upon genotypic composition of sex chromosomes.

definition.value: Note that the chromosomal constitution of genotypic sex varies in different organisms. In human, we have XY, XX, though abnormal XXY, X0, XYY, and other combinations are possible.

value.value: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual based upon genotypic composition that confers the capability for an organism to differentiate male gonads.

definition.value: Note that the chromosomal constitution of genotypic sex varies in different organisms. In human, this would be XY, though abnormal XXY and XYY would also result in a male phenotypic outcome.

value.value: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population based upon genotypic composition that confers the capability for an organism to differentiate female gonads.

definition.value: Note that the chromosomal constitution of genotypic sex varies in different organisms. In human, this would be XX, though abnormal X0 and XXX would also result in a female phenotypic outcome.
